                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d18">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum.</hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">[Handed to the Chinese minister, Mr. Wu, by Acting Secretary Hill,
                    September 11, 1900.]</p>
                <p>The United States does not feel called upon to express any opinion at this time
                    as to the sufficiency of Li Hung Chang’s authority, but hopes it will transpire
                    that his credentials are full and authoritative, not only for negotiation, but
                    to enable him without further delay to give assurance that the life and property
                    of Americans will henceforth be respected throughout the Chinese Empire.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-09-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 11, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
